chment','image/png',0),(463,9,'2017-03-11 13:34:58','2017-03-11 13:34:58','','13.2','','inherit','open','closed','','13-2-3','','','2017-03-11 13:34:58','2017-03-11 13:34:58','',133,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.2-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(464,9,'2017-03-11 13:35:06','2017-03-11 13:35:06','','header','','inherit','open','closed','','header-7','','','2017-03-11 13:35:06','2017-03-11 13:35:06','',133,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/header-3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(465,9,'2017-03-11 13:49:06','2017-03-11 13:49:06','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n<h2> The Nursery Station</h2>\n<p>AFTER TWO WEEKS, YOUR SEEDLINGS ARE READY FOR THEIR FIRST TRANSPLANT.. THEY\nWILL SPEND THE NEXT TWO TO FOUR WEEKS IN A SMALLER \"FLOATING ROOT\" SYSTEM.\nWE CALL THIS SMALLER VERSION \'THE NURSERY\'. ONCE YOUR PLANTS BEGIN TO SHADE\nONE ANOTHER, THEY ARE READY TO TRANSPLANT FROM \"THE NURSERY\" INTO THE LARGER\nSYSTEM DEPICTED IN SECTION 3.</p>\n\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n\n<h2>MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.1-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.2-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n<h2>TOOLS:</h2>\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.1-1.png\" alt=\"\"  width=100% />\n\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n\n\n<h2> Building nursery station\n</h2>\n<p>\nWITH THE SCRAP WOOD YOU HAVE, BUILD A BOX SIMILAR TO THIS ONE.\nTHE Styrofoam Board SHOULD JUST inside of it. use woodblock\nin the corners to support the board.</p>\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/6-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=100% />\n<p>OPEN AT LEAST TWO TRASH BAGS WITH A CUTTER AND MAKE IT FLAT..\nTHEN PLACE THEM INSIDE THE BOX YOU HAVE CREATED. THEY NEED TO HOLD the\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION. MAKE SURE TO fix trash bags to the wooden container\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it 