x trash bags to the wooden container\r\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it is water tight.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/7-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/8-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Nursery Station: FIRST TRANSPLANT</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/10-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/12-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nTHIS IS what YOUR SET UP SHOULD LOOK LIKE when it is complete and fully planted.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.','FIRST TRANSPLANT','','inherit','closed','closed','','133-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 19:34:08','2017-03-12 19:34:08','',133,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/133-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(490,1,'2017-03-12 19:36:43','2017-03-12 19:36:43','','2017-03-12_22-27-25','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-03-12_22-27-25','','','2017-03-12 19:36:43','2017-03-12 19:36:43','',143,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/2017-03-12_22-27-25.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(491,1,'2017-03-12 19:37:02','2017-03-12 19:37:02','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TOOLS:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.1-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.2-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>PREPARING THE FOAM BOARD</h2>\r\nUSE THE PLASTIC CUP TO DEFINE SPACING\r\nAND POSITION OF YOUR PLANT. KEEP IN MIND\r\nTHE SIZE OF THE PLANTS AS THEY GROW!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Building THe floating root system.</h2>\r\nWITH THE SCRAP WOOD (i.e. from pallets) YOU HAVE, BUILD A BOX SIMILAR TO\r\nThe Nursery Station - Although this system is bigger,\r\nIt will Hold less Plants. This is to give your plants adequate\r\nspace to Prevent them from Shading one Another and Affecting\r\nEach Other\'s Growth.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/6-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nOPEN AT LEAST TWO TRASH BAGS WITH A CUTTER AND MAKE IT FLAT..\r\nTHEN PLACE THEM INSIDE THE BOX YOU HAVE CREATED. THEY NEED TO HOLD the\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION. MAKE SURE TO fix trash bags to the wooden container\r\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it is water tight.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/7-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TRANSPLANTING SEEDLINGS</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/8-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">THE SEEDLING IS READY TO\r\nBE TRANSPLANTED INTO ANY\r\nHYDROPONIC SYSTEM.</p>\r\nNOW YOU CAN PUT\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION\r\n&amp; water INSIDE\r\nTHE BOX. PLACE\r\nTHE PLANTS ON TOP\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/10-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11.1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.','SECOND TRANSPLANT AND HARVESTING','','inherit','closed','closed','','143-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 19:37:02','2017-03-12 19:37:02','',143,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/143-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(492,1,'2017-03-12 19:37:42','2017-03-12 19:37:42','','2017-03-12_22-32-01','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-03-12_22-32-01','','','2017-03-12 19:37:42','2017-03-12 19:37:42','',275,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/2017-03-12_22-32-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(493,1,'2017-03-12 19:38:08','2017-03-12 19:38:08','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Ce dont on a boisson:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-3.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-3.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Des outils:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-4.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-4.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Preparer le plateau en polystyrene</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Utiliser le gobelet plastique pour definir la\r\ndisposition des plantes (position et distance).\r\nIl faut pas oublier la taille des plantes qui poussent.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Construir un systeme des racines flottantes</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec des dechets de bois (ex. des palettes) il faut construire une\r\nboite semblable a la pepiniere - sauf que ce systeme - ci est plus grand.\r\nOn va y mettre moins de plantes parce que les plantes ont besoin d\'assez\r\nde place pour ne pas faire d\'ombre.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec un cutter ouvrir et aplatir au moins deux sacs poubelle pour mettre\r\ndans la boite deja construite. Le plastique doit contenir la solution\r\nnutritive. Il faut bien fixer le plastique a la boite de bois avec des\r\nagrafes ou des punaises pour assurer que la construction soit etanche (impermeable).</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La Transplantation des jeunes Plants</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Le jeune plant est pret pour\r\nla transplantation n\'importe\r\nquel systeme hydroponique.</p>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">On peut maintenant\r\nverser dans la boite\r\nl\'eau avec de la\r\nsolution nutritive.\r\nMettre les plants\r\ndessus.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-11.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Concept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io</p>\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.','FAIRE LA DEUXIEME TRANSPLANTATION ET LA RECOLTE','','inherit','closed','closed','','275-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 19:38:08','2017-03-12 19:38:08','',275,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/275-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(494,1,'2017-03-12 19:39:09','2017-03-12 19:39:09','','2017-03-12_22-30-09','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-03-12_22-30-09','','','2017-03-12 19:39:09','2017-03-12 19:39:09','',273,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/2017-03-12_22-30-09.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(495,1,'2017-03-12 19:39:26','2017-03-12 19:39:26','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La pepiniere</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Au bout de deux semaines, on peut faire la premiere\r\ntransplantation. Des jeunes plants qui vont passer les prochaines\r\ndeux a quatre semaines dans un systeme plus petit des racines\r\nflottantes. Le systeme s\'appelle la pepiniere. Une fois les plantes\r\ncommencent a se faire de l\'ombre, on peut les transplanter de la\r\npepiniere et dans le systeme plus grand represente en section 3.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Ce dont on a boisson:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/4.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/4.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Des outils:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/5.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/5.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Construir la pepiniere</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\" style=\"text-align: right;\">avec le bout de bois construir une boite comme celle ci-dessous. Le\r\nplateau de polystyrene dont etre a l\'interieur. Mettre un bloc de bois\r\ndans chaque coin pour soutenir le plateau.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec un cutter ouvrir et aplatir au moins deux sacs poubelle pour mettre dans la\r\nboite deja construite. Le plastique doit contenir la solution nutritive. Il faut\r\nbien fixer le plastique a la boite de bois avec des agrafes ou des punaises pour\r\nassurer que la construction soit etanche (impermeable).</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La pepiniere: la premiere transplantation</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/12.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Voila une representation d\'une installation achevee et pleinement plantee.</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/13.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/13.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.','FARRE LA PREMIERE TRANSPLANTATION','','inherit','closed','closed','','273-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 19:39:26','2017-03-12 19:39:26','',273,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/273-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(501,1,'2017-03-12 20:22:26','2017-03-12 20:22:26','[aqh]','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home-en','','','2017-03-12 21:20:36','2017-03-12 21:20:36','',0,'http://85.195.95.236/?page_id=501',0,'page','',0),(502,1,'2017-03-12 20:22:26','2017-03-12 20:22:26','[aqh]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','501-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 20:22:26','2017-03-12 20:22:26','',501,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/501-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(503,1,'2017-03-12 20:23:37','2017-03-12 20:23:37','[aqh]','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home-es','','','2017-03-12 21:22:35','2017-03-12 21:22:35','',0,'http://85.195.95.236/?page_id=503',0,'page','',0),(504,1,'2017-03-12 20:23:37','2017-03-12 20:23:37','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','503-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 20:23:37','2017-03-12 20:23:37','',503,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/503-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(506,1,'2017-03-12 20:25:29','2017-03-12 20:25:29','[aqh]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','503-revision-v1','','','2017-03-12 20:25:29','2017-03-12 20:25:29','',503,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/503-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(507,1,'2017-03-12 20:26:17','2017-03-12 20:26:17','[aqh]'