7-03-13 08:28:35','2017-03-13 08:28:35','',267,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_1_III_french.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(572,9,'2017-03-13 08:28:44','2017-03-13 08:28:44','','HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III_french','','inherit','open','closed','','how_to_hydroponics_2_iii_french','','','2017-03-13 08:28:44','2017-03-13 08:28:44','',267,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III_french.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(573,9,'2017-03-13 08:28:55','2017-03-13 08:28:55','','HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III_french','','inherit','open','closed','','how_to_hydroponics_3_iii_french','','','2017-03-13 08:28:55','2017-03-13 08:28:55','',267,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III_french.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(574,9,'2017-03-13 08:29:54','2017-03-13 08:29:54','<img width=\"100%\" class=\"page-background\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.1.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Ce dont on a besoin:</h2>\r\n\r\n<img width=\"100%\" class=\"page-background\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.3.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n\r\n <h2 class=\"page-header-1\">1. Préparer le substrat</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Pour hydroponie, des autres substances remplacent la terre. Ces\r\nsubstances s\'appellent substrats. Des options suivent ci-dessous.</p>\r\n<img width=\"100%\" class=\"page-background\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.4.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n\r\n <h2 class=\"page-header-1\">2. Planter les graines</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Faire un trou de .5\r\ncentim?tres de profondeur\r\navec un doigt ou un stylo.\r\nIntroduire une graine\r\net couvrir l?g?rement.</p>\r\n<img width=\"100%\" class=\"page-background\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.5.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">\r\n?viter de faire des trous trop\r\nprofonds ou les graines ne recevront\r\npas assez de soleil. Et ?viter de\r\nfaire des trous peu profonds ou on\r\nrisque de noyer les graines quand on\r\narrose.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n <h2 class=\"page-header-1\">3. Faire germer les jeunes plants</h2>\r\n<p>Placer le bac dans une lumière de soleil diffuse.\r\nAprès quelques jours, les plants commenceront à germer.\r\nArroser suffisamment de manière à garder le substrat humide..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les jeunes plants aiment l\'humidité!\r\nCouvrir avec du plastique transparent\r\nou avec de l\'essuie tout mouillé\r\npour augmenter l\'humidité..</p>\r\n<img width=\"100%\" class=\"page-background\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.6.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n<p>\r\nLaisser couvert pour les\r\ntrois premiers jours ou jusqu\'à\r\nce qu\'on voit les nouveaux germes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">\r\nArroser une fois par jour\r\navec de la solution nutritive\r\nà moitié degré.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n <h2 class=\"page-header-1\">\r\n        4. Les details de la culture hydroponique\r\n      </h2>\r\n      <h3 class=\"table-header\">Le cycle des cultures</h3>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"table-container\">\r\n        <table class=\"page-table\" data-kind=\"l\'?t?\">\r\n          <thead class=\"page-table__thead\">\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__thead-tr\">\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Variete*<br class=\"visible-1024\"> </th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Premiere<br class=\"visible-1024\">Transplantation</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Deuxieme <br class=\"visible-1024\">Transplantation</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Recolte<br class=\"visible-1024\"> </th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </thead>\r\n          <tbody>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Laitue</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jeunes legumes verts</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Pas de transplantation</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   28</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Epices</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Legumes verts asiatiques</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   21</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   35</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Legumes verts rustiques</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"table-container\">\r\n        <table class=\"page-table\" data-kind=\"l\'hiver\">\r\n          <thead class=\"page-table__thead\">\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Variete*<br class=\"visible-1024\"> </th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Premiere<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplantation</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Deuxieme<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplantation</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Recolte<br class=\"visible-1024\"> </th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </thead>\r\n          <tbody>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Laitue</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jeunes legumes verts</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Pas de transplantation</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Epices</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Legumes verts asiatiques</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Legumes verts rustiques</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Jours   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <section class=\"page-section\">\r\n        <h4>\r\n          Solution Mixing Instructions<br>\r\n          (Using Molina Salts)\r\n        </h4>\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__note\">\r\n          Note: Our nutrient solution contains two parts; A & B. Follow instructions below to make them.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n          <h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\">Solution A</h5>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolve in 5 liters of water:</div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--green\">Nitrato de potasio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--orange\">Nitrato de amonio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--salmon\">Superfosfato triple</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n          <h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\">Solution B</h5>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolve in 2 liters of water:</div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--yellow\">Sulfato de magnesio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--pink\">Micronutrientes</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--brown\">Quelato de hierro</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n      </section>\r\n\r\n      <section class=\"page-section\">\r\n        <h4>Nutrient Solution Recipes</h4>\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__text\">\r\n          For every liter of water add both 5 mL of <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solution A</span> & 2 mL <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solution B</span>.\r\n           Use syringe to measure exact amounts.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img class=\"page-section__image\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.7.png\" alt=\"\">\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__note\">\r\n          Note: For seedlings, use half-strength solution.<br>\r\n          2.5 mL of Solution A & 1 mL of Solution B\r\n        </div>\r\n      </section>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"page-footnotes\">\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__header\">\r\n          * Varietes\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Laitue:</span> laitue romaine, laitue bibb, feuille de chene, batavia\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Jeunes legumes verts:</span> Arugula, Spinach, Mixed Lettuce, Water Cress\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Epices:</span> Basil, Cilantro, Parsely, Mint, Sage\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Legumes verts asiatiques:</span> Bok Choy, Tatsoi, Mustard Greens, Mizuna\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Legumes verts asiatiques:</span> Swiss Chard, Spinach, Kale & Chicory\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top:10px;\"></div>\r\n<p>Concept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDesign, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_1_III_french.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','CULTIVER LES JEUNES PLANTS','','inherit','closed','closed','','267-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:29:54','2017-03-13 08:29:54','',267,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(575,9,'2017-03-13 08:31:24','2017-03-13 08:31:24','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La pepiniere</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Au bout de deux semaines, on peut faire la premiere\r\ntransplantation. Des jeunes plants qui vont passer les prochaines\r\ndeux a quatre semaines dans un systeme plus petit des racines\r\nflottantes. Le systeme s\'appelle la pepiniere. Une fois les plantes\r\ncommencent a se faire de l\'ombre, on peut les transplanter de la\r\npepiniere et dans le systeme plus grand represente en section 3.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Ce dont on a boisson:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/4.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/4.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Des outils:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/5.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/5.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Construir la pepiniere</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\" style=\"text-align: right;\">avec le bout de bois construir une boite comme celle ci-dessous. Le\r\nplateau de polystyrene dont etre a l\'interieur. Mettre un bloc de bois\r\ndans chaque coin pour soutenir le plateau.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec un cutter ouvrir et aplatir au moins deux sacs poubelle pour mettre dans la\r\nboite deja construite. Le plastique doit contenir la solution nutritive. Il faut\r\nbien fixer le plastique a la boite de bois avec des agrafes ou des punaises pour\r\nassurer que la construction soit etanche (impermeable).</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La pepiniere: la premiere transplantation</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/12.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Voila une representation d\'une installation achevee et pleinement plantee.</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/13.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/13.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III_french.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','FARRE LA PREMIERE TRANSPLANTATION','','inherit','closed','closed','','273-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:31:24','2017-03-13 08:31:24','',273,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/273-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(576,9,'2017-03-13 08:33:27','2017-03-13 08:33:27','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Ce dont on a boisson:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-3.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-3.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Des outils:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-4.1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-4.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Preparer le plateau en polystyrene</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Utiliser le gobelet plastique pour definir la\r\ndisposition des plantes (position et distance).\r\nIl faut pas oublier la taille des plantes qui poussent.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">Construir un systeme des racines flottantes</h2>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec des dechets de bois (ex. des palettes) il faut construire une\r\nboite semblable a la pepiniere - sauf que ce systeme - ci est plus grand.\r\nOn va y mettre moins de plantes parce que les plantes ont besoin d\'assez\r\nde place pour ne pas faire d\'ombre.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Avec un cutter ouvrir et aplatir au moins deux sacs poubelle pour mettre\r\ndans la boite deja construite. Le plastique doit contenir la solution\r\nnutritive. Il faut bien fixer le plastique a la boite de bois avec des\r\nagrafes ou des punaises pour assurer que la construction soit etanche (impermeable).</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">La Transplantation des jeunes Plants</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Le jeune plant est pret pour\r\nla transplantation n\'importe\r\nquel systeme hydroponique.</p>\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">On peut maintenant\r\nverser dans la boite\r\nl\'eau avec de la\r\nsolution nutritive.\r\nMettre les plants\r\ndessus.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-11.1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/3-11.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p class=\"page-text\">Concept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io</p>\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III_french.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','FAIRE LA DEUXIEME TRANSPLANTATION ET LA RECOLTE','','inherit','closed','closed','','275-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:33:27','2017-03-13 08:33:27','',275,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/275-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(577,9,'2017-03-13 08:37:41','2017-03-13 08:37:41','','HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_1_III','','inherit','open','closed','','how_to_hydroponics_1_iii','','','2017-03-13 08:37:41','2017-03-13 08:37:41','',76,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_1_III.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(578,9,'2017-03-13 08:37:49','2017-03-13 08:37:49','','HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III','','inherit','open','closed','','how_to_hydroponics_2_iii','','','2017-03-13 08:37:49','2017-03-13 08:37:49','',76,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(579,9,'2017-03-13 08:38:02','2017-03-13 08:38:02','','HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III','','inherit','open','closed','','how_to_hydroponics_3_iii','','','2017-03-13 08:38:02','2017-03-13 08:38:02','',76,'http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(580,9,'2017-03-13 08:38:49','2017-03-13 08:38:49','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.1-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\"  />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.3-2.png\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\"> 1. Preparing the substrate</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nin hydroponics, other matierals are used to replace soil.\r\nWe call these materials \'substrates\'.\r\nlist of examples below: </p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.4-2.png\" width=\"100%\"  />\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">2. Planting seeds </h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">\r\nMake a hole o.5 cm deep\r\nwith finger or pen\r\ninsert seed & cover lightly\r\n</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.5-2.png\" width=\"100%\"  />\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">avoid making the holes too deep.\r\nThis will prevent the seeds\r\nfrom getting proper sunlight.\r\nAlso avoid making holes too\r\nshallow. Seeds may wash away\r\nwhile watering. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">3. Germinating seedlings</h2>\r\n<p>place tray in indirect sunlight\r\nafter a few days. plants willstart sprouting.\r\nwater gently & keep substrate moist.</p>\r\n<p>seedlings like humidity!\r\ncover with transparent plastic\r\nor wet paper towel to\r\nincrease humidity.</p>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.6-2.png\" width=\"100%\"  />\r\n<p>leave cover on.\r\nfor the first 3 days or\r\nuntil the first leaves sprout.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">water once a day with\r\nhalf-strength nutrient solution\r\nsee pg.7 for detalis</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"page-header-1\">\r\n        4. Hydroponic Growing Details\r\n      </h2>\r\n      <h3 class=\"table-header\">Growing Cycle</h3>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"table-container\">\r\n        <table class=\"page-table\" data-kind=\"SUMMER\">\r\n          <thead class=\"page-table__thead\">\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__thead-tr\">\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Crop<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Variety*</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">First<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplant</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Second<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplant</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Harvest<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Time</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </thead>\r\n          <tbody>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Head Lettuce</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Baby Greens</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">No transplant</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   28</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Spices</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Asian Greens</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   7</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   35</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Hearty Greenst</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"table-container\">\r\n        <table class=\"page-table\" data-kind=\"Winter\">\r\n          <thead class=\"page-table__thead\">\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Crop<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Variety*</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">First<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplant</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Second<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Transplant</th>\r\n              <th class=\"page-table__th\">Harvest<br class=\"visible-1024\"> Time</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </thead>\r\n          <tbody>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Head Lettuce</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Baby Greens</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">No transplant</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Spices</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Asian Greens</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   42</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr class=\"page-table__tr\">\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Hearty Greens</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   14</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   21-28</td>\r\n              <td class=\"page-table__td\">Days   56</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n          </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <section class=\"page-section\">\r\n        <h4>\r\n          Solution Mixing Instructions<br>\r\n          (Using Molina Salts)\r\n        </h4>\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__note\">\r\n          Note: Our nutrient solution contains two parts; A & B. Follow instructions below to make then.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n          <h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\">Solution A</h5>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolve in 5 liters of water:</div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--green\">Nitrato de potasio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--orange\">Nitrato de amonio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--salmon\">Superfosfato triple</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n          <h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\">Solution B</h5>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolve in 2 liters of water:</div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--yellow\">Sulfato de magnesio</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--pink\">Micronutrientes</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"page-section__solution-step\">\r\n            1 bag x <div class=\"page-section__color-box page-section__color-box--brown\">Quelato de hierro</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n      </section>\r\n\r\n      <section class=\"page-section\">\r\n        <h4>Nutrient Solution Recipes</h4>\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__text\">\r\n          For every liter of water add both 5 mL of <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solution A</span> & 2 mL <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solution B</span>.\r\n          Use syringe to measure exaсt amounts.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img class=\"page-section__image\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.7-2.png\" width=\"100%\" >\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-section__note\">\r\n          Note: For seedlings, use half-strength solution.<br>\r\n          2.5 mL of Solution A & 1 mL of Solution B\r\n        </div>\r\n      </section>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"page-footnotes\">\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__header\">\r\n          * Crop Varieties\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Head Lettuce:</span> Romaine, Butterhead, Oakleaf, Batavia\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Baby Greens:</span> Arugula, Spinach, Mixed Lettuce, Water Cress\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Spices:</span> Basil, Cilantro, Parsely, Mint, Sage\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Asian Greens:</span> Bok Choy, Tatsoi, Mustard Greens, Mizuna\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n          <span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">Hearty Greens:</span> Swiss Chard, Spinach, Kale & Chicory\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-top:10px;\"></div>\r\n<p>Concept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDesign, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_1_III.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','GROWING SEEDLINGS','','inherit','closed','closed','','76-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:38:49','2017-03-13 08:38:49','',76,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/76-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(581,9,'2017-03-13 08:39:45','2017-03-13 08:39:45','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>The Nursery Station</h2>\r\nAFTER TWO WEEKS, YOUR SEEDLINGS ARE READY FOR THEIR FIRST TRANSPLANT.. THEY\r\nWILL SPEND THE NEXT TWO TO FOUR WEEKS IN A SMALLER \"FLOATING ROOT\" SYSTEM.\r\nWE CALL THIS SMALLER VERSION \'THE NURSERY\'. ONCE YOUR PLANTS BEGIN TO SHADE\r\nONE ANOTHER, THEY ARE READY TO TRANSPLANT FROM \"THE NURSERY\" INTO THE LARGER\r\nSYSTEM DEPICTED IN SECTION 3.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.1-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.2-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TOOLS:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Building nursery station</h2>\r\nWITH THE SCRAP WOOD YOU HAVE, BUILD A BOX SIMILAR TO THIS ONE.\r\nTHE Styrofoam Board SHOULD JUST inside of it. use woodblock\r\nin the corners to support the board.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/6-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nOPEN AT LEAST TWO TRASH BAGS WITH A CUTTER AND MAKE IT FLAT..\r\nTHEN PLACE THEM INSIDE THE BOX YOU HAVE CREATED. THEY NEED TO HOLD the\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION. MAKE SURE TO fix trash bags to the wooden container\r\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it is water tight.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/7-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/8-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Nursery Station: FIRST TRANSPLANT</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/10-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/12-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nTHIS IS what YOUR SET UP SHOULD LOOK LIKE when it is complete and fully planted.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_2_III.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','FIRST TRANSPLANT','','inherit','closed','closed','','133-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:39:45','2017-03-13 08:39:45','',133,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/133-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(582,9,'2017-03-13 08:40:49','2017-03-13 08:40:49','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TOOLS:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.1-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.2-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>PREPARING THE FOAM BOARD</h2>\r\nUSE THE PLASTIC CUP TO DEFINE SPACING\r\nAND POSITION OF YOUR PLANT. KEEP IN MIND\r\nTHE SIZE OF THE PLANTS AS THEY GROW!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Building THe floating root system.</h2>\r\nWITH THE SCRAP WOOD (i.e. from pallets) YOU HAVE, BUILD A BOX SIMILAR TO\r\nThe Nursery Station - Although this system is bigger,\r\nIt will Hold less Plants. This is to give your plants adequate\r\nspace to Prevent them from Shading one Another and Affecting\r\nEach Other\'s Growth.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/6-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nOPEN AT LEAST TWO TRASH BAGS WITH A CUTTER AND MAKE IT FLAT..\r\nTHEN PLACE THEM INSIDE THE BOX YOU HAVE CREATED. THEY NEED TO HOLD the\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION. MAKE SURE TO fix trash bags to the wooden container\r\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it is water tight.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/7-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TRANSPLANTING SEEDLINGS</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/8-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">THE SEEDLING IS READY TO\r\nBE TRANSPLANTED INTO ANY\r\nHYDROPONIC SYSTEM.</p>\r\nNOW YOU CAN PUT\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION\r\n&amp; water INSIDE\r\nTHE BOX. PLACE\r\nTHE PLANTS ON TOP\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/10-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11.1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nConcept by\r\nIsabel Inc.\r\nwww.isabel.io\r\n\r\nConcept, Design, Illustrations by\r\nAntonio Scarponi / [onceptual)evices\r\nwww.conceptualdevices.com\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HOW_TO_HYDROPONICS_3_III.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>','SECOND TRANSPLANT AND HARVESTING','','inherit','closed','closed','','143-revision-v1','','','2017-03-13 08:40:49','2017-03-13 08:40:49','',143,'http://85.195.95.236/index.php/143-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(592,1,'2017-03-22 18:04:52','0000-00-00 00:00:00','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_video link=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3lTjJTt_IAY\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2017-03-22 18:04:52','2017-03-22 18:04:52','',0,'http://35.198.69.129:8080/?p=592',0,'post','',0),(602,1,'2017-03-28 18:47:42','2017-03-28 18:47:42','[aqe]','Ask an Expert (mobile)','','publish','closed','closed',