ge-footnotes__note\"><strong><span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">   Verduras de hoja Asiaticas:</span> </strong>Bok Choy, Tatsoi, Hojas de Mostaza, Mizuna</div>\r\n<div class=\"page-footnotes__note\"><strong><span class=\"page-footnotes__note-header\">   Verduras Abundantes:</span> </strong>Acelgas, Espinaca, Kale</div>\r\n<h3>5. Instrucciones de mezcla de Solución\r\n(Usando Sales de La Molina)</h3>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__note\"><em><strong>Nota:</strong> Nuestra solución de nutriente contiene dos partes A y B. Siga las instrucciones de abajo para hacerlas.</em></div>\r\n<section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n<h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\"><strong>Solución A</strong></h5>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolver en 5 litros de agua:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x Nitrato de potasio</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x Nitrato de amonio</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x Superfosfato triple</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section><section class=\"page-section__solution\">\r\n<h5 class=\"page-section__solution-header\"><strong>Solución B</strong></h5>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__steps-header\">Disolver en 2 litros de agua:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x <em>Sulfato de magnesio</em></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x <em>Micronutrientes</em></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"page-section__solution-step\">1 bolsa x <em>Quelato de hierro</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section></section>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__solution-step\"></div>\r\n<section class=\"page-section\">[embed]https://youtu.be/kbSe6WDVJdk&w=350[/embed]\r\n<h4>Receta de Solución de Nutrientes</h4>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__text\">Por cada litro de agua añada 5 mL de <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solución A</span> y 2 de mL <span class=\"page-section__text-bold\">Solución B</span>. Use una jeringa para tener las medidas exactas.</div>\r\n</section></div>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__text\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-85 size-full\" src=\"http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.7.png\" width=\"422\" height=\"257\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__text\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Nota: Para las plántulas, use la mitad de la solución.</em>\r\n<em>2.5 mL de Solución A y 1 mL de Solución B</em></div>\r\n<div class=\"page-section__text\" style=\"text-align: right;\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"page-footnotes__note\">\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">Concept by</div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">Isabel Inc.</div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">www.isabel.io</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">Concept, Design, Illustrations by</div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">Antonio Scarponi / <span class=\"footer-content__text-bold\">[onceptual)evices</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">www.conceptualdevices.com</div>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\">\r\n\r\n© World Food Program, 2016.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3 class=\"footer-content__line\"><a href=\"http://85.195.95.236/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/p1b441f22717bn1hv9d4o1g2g131t4.pdf\">Download manual in PDF</a></h3>\r\n<div class=\"footer-content__line\"></div>','PLANTANDO SEMILLAS','','inherit','closed','closed','','259-revision-v1','','','2017-04-04 23:52:17','2017-04-04 23:52:17','',259,'http://35.198.69.129:8080/index.php/259-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(658,6,'2017-04-05 00:41:51','2017-04-05 00:41:51','<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>The Nursery Station</h2>\r\nAFTER TWO WEEKS, YOUR SEEDLINGS ARE READY FOR THEIR FIRST TRANSPLANT.. THEY\r\nWILL SPEND THE NEXT TWO TO FOUR WEEKS IN A SMALLER \"FLOATING ROOT\" SYSTEM.\r\nWE CALL THIS SMALLER VERSION \'THE NURSERY\'. ONCE YOUR PLANTS BEGIN TO SHADE\r\nONE ANOTHER, THEY ARE READY TO TRANSPLANT FROM \"THE NURSERY\" INTO THE LARGER\r\nSYSTEM DEPICTED IN SECTION 3.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/3-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nxr4EoacXpc&w=350[/embed]\r\n<h2>MATERIALS YOU NEED:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.1-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/4.2-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>TOOLS:</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5.2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Building nursery station</h2>\r\nWITH THE SCRAP WOOD YOU HAVE, BUILD A BOX SIMILAR TO THIS ONE.\r\nTHE Styrofoam Board SHOULD JUST inside of it. use woodblock\r\nin the corners to support the board.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/6-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nOPEN AT LEAST TWO TRASH BAGS WITH A CUTTER AND MAKE IT FLAT..\r\nTHEN PLACE THEM INSIDE THE BOX YOU HAVE CREATED. THEY NEED TO HOLD the\r\nNUTRIENT SOLUTION. MAKE SURE TO fix trash bags to the wooden container\r\nwith staples or pins to ensure that it is water tight.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/7-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/8-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2>Nursery Station: FIRST TRANSPLANT</h2>\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/10-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/11-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/12-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\nTHIS IS what YOUR SET UP SHOULD LOOK LIKE when it is complete and fully planted.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/13.